ODM Leader Raila Odinga kisses his wife Ida during the Launch of Azimio la Umoja National Convention at Moi International Sports complex Kasarani Stadium on December 10, 2021. [Boniface okendo,Standard]  Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) leader Raila Odinga arrived in Mombasa on Tuesday afternoon for a three-day vacation.  In a brief phone interview, Raila said he was advised to rest after a vigorous campaign in various parts of the country before the launch of his presidential bid on December 10 at Kasarani in Nairobi.  "I'm in Mombasa to rest for three days. I've not held any meeting today," said Raila who sounded excited and ready for gruelling campaigns ahead of the 2022 polls.  The ODM leader who is expected to launch the second phase of his campaigns in the next few days said he had not held talks with any other political groups since he launched the campaigns. "I was advised to rest after Kasarani. After the three days I will talk to different people and groups," he said, adding that he was working on a national movement that will alter the course of the country's political and economic landscape.  He said he wants to bring everybody on board for the good of the country. Raila said he will reach out to everybody but form a government with those ready to fight ill affecting the nation.  By Phares Mutembei | 10 minutes ago By Nathan Ochunge and Jackline Inyanji | 10 minutes ago By Patrick Beja and Nehemiah Okwembah | 10 minutes ago By Renson Mnyamwezi and Phares Mutembei | 10 minutes ago Enjoy unlimited access to The Standard website at a 50% discount on the yearly plan.